  <title>IDE terminal integration</title>

  <p>When you open a workspace with an IDE, Podbx writes
  <file>.podbx/podbx-shell.sh</file> into the project and configures the
  editor's integrated terminal to use it. Every terminal tab you open in
  the IDE transparently enters the <code>podbx-os</code> container.</p>

  <p>If the IDE is installed as a Flatpak, Podbx also grants it the
  <code>org.freedesktop.Flatpak</code> permission so it can reach the host
  container through <cmd>flatpak-spawn --host</cmd>.</p>

</page>
